name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
address: 1235 North Post St. Suite 201, Spokane WA, 99205
vaccines: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine or the single dose of the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. *** All patients 12 years old and older can register regardless of phase for Pfizer only... Johnson and Johnson is for 18 years and older. (If 12-17 years old for Pfizer you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. Enter the building at the time of your appointment only. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 1750 112th Avenue Northeast, STE C-102, Bellevue WA, 98004
info:
At the Hawker Center, we provide a warm oasis of peace and comfort, treating our patients and their stories with patience and respect. Imagine a spa-like atmosphere where a highly-trained doctor or nurse is administrating the COVID19 vaccination. That’s the Hawker Center difference.
***We currently are providing the 1st and 2nd doses of MODERNA.*** Please sign up for an appointment time.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction.***If you would like to find out more information about our clinic, please visit our website at www.hawkerhealth.com***

name: Pliable, LLC Covid-19 Vaccine Site
address: Renton Technical College Cafeteria | 3000 NE 4th Street, Renton WA, 98056
vaccines: Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 Vaccine, Janssen COVID-19 Vaccine
info:
Hello! We warmly welcome you to Pliable’s mobile COVID-19 vaccination clinic at Renton Technical College in Renton, Washington on Thursday, May 27th, 2021. This vaccination event is administering the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine. This is a two-dose vaccination series.
.
If you have had your 1st dose, please bring your CDC vaccination card with you to your 2nd-dose appointment.
.
Schedule your 2nd dose at Renton Technical College on June 17th here: https://prepmod.doh.wa.gov//appointment/en/reg/6055129693
.
.
Pliable LLC is a nurse practitioner-led organization for mindfully-driven healthcare. In alignment with Washington State Department of Health’s (DOH) equitable COVID-19 vaccine distribution strategies, our goal is to equitably and compassionately serve those communities disproportionately impacted by COVID-19 and help fill in vaccine access gaps. 
.
.
.
Please read the CDC and WA DOH information regarding COVID-19 Vaccinations and Pfizer-BioNTech and have your questions answered BEFORE REGISTERING. Resources can be found at: https://www.doh.wa.gov/Emergencies/COVID19/Vaccine https://www.cdc.gov/vaccines/covid-19/info-by-product/pfizer/pfizer-bioNTech-faqs.html 
The American Academy of Pediatrics’ Endorsement & Facts can be found at: https://www.aappublications.org/news/2021/05/12/cdc-aap-pfizer-covid-vaccine-teens-051221.
.
You/Legal Guardian should have accessed and read the EUA fact sheet prior to registering. 
.
The Fact Sheet for this vaccination can be found at: https://www.fda.gov/media/144414/download 
.
For resources on side effects and post vaccination expectations: https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/vaccines/expect/after.html
.
By proceeding and scheduling online you are consenting to the following terms below as the patient or surrogate decision maker for the patient, including minors. 
• I certify that I am/my child is at least 12 years of age. 
• I understand it is not possible to predict all possible side effects or complications associated with receiving the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine. 
• I understand the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) has authorized the emergency use of this vaccine, which is not an FDA approved vaccine in this patient population. I understand the nature, alternatives, benefits and risks of vaccination, to the extent they are known at this time. 
• I am encouraged to sign up with v-safe: https://vsafe.cdc.gov/ 
• I acknowledge that I have been advised to remain near the vaccination location for observation for 15 minutes after administration, 30 mins if I have a prior history of allergic reactions to vaccines. 
• I give my consent to Pliable LLC, including licensed employees, volunteers, and partners, to administer the Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine as described above. 
• I authorize and understand Pliable LLC may be required to or may voluntarily disclose my vaccine-related health information to my insurance plan, state or federal registries, and/or other public health authorities, for purposes of payment or health care operations. 
• I understand that I am not creating a patient relationship with Pliable LLC by participating in vaccination. I understand Pliable LLC is not acting as my medical provider. Vaccination does not replace treatment by my medical provider. I agree I will seek medical advice, care and treatment from a medical provider if I have questions or concerns, or if I experience side effects. 
• I have been provided expectations for the day of my vaccination.
• I acknowledge that I have read the Pfizer-BioNTech Fact Sheet and agree to these terms and conditions. 
.
On the day of your appointment: 
• Registration and attestation serves as consent. Minors will NOT need to bring a formal signed parental consent on day of clinic.  
• Vaccination is available regardless of your citizenship or immigration status. 
• If you have insurance, please include this information during your online registration. Insurance is NOT required, you will not be billed, the vaccination is FREE TO ALL. Insurance will cover administrative costs if available. 
• Wear a short-sleeved shirt or clothing that allows access to your upper arm. • Masks are required at all times at the clinic. If you do not have a mask one will be provided to you. 
• Please arrive no earlier than 10 minutes prior to your scheduled appointment time. Appointment cannot be guaranteed if you arrive late. • Do not visit the site if you are experiencing symptoms of COVID-19 on the day of your appointment. 
• If you have a history of serious allergic reactions (anaphylaxis) and are prescribed an epinephrine auto injector (Epipen, etc) please bring this to your vaccination appointment and notify clinical staff. 
.
HAPPY VACCINATION DAY!
.
www.bepliable.com
.
If you need to cancel, please click on “Cancel” link in your confirmation email. If you need to change your appointment time, please click on “Reschedule” in your confirmation email link to check if there are other time slots available. If you need to change the date, cancel this appointment and schedule another one. We cannot guarantee that you will be able to reschedule for the desired date and time.

This confirms your appointment but does not guarantee you have met all criteria to receive your vaccine. Any appointment which is made by a patient who is not eligible based upon current vaccine eligibility will be cancelled prior to the date of the clinic.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Olequa Winlock Senior Center Clinic
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in. Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements. This clinic is located at and hosted by Olequa Winlock Senior Center in partnership with Lewis County Public Health and Social Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-up location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
